8sJNa36JgGgmcHpd-MvowA.text: Had to get me some authentic fish and chips, and thankfully Cheap Eats promised us some very close to our B&B. I had a nice hunk of cod and a Carlsberg lager on tap.  The breading was so light and airy -- must have been fried REALLY hot in some extra clean oil.  It was great!  Martin had the Rockfish, and his was huge.  He did manage to eat it all.  He said the quality was quite good, and those fryers knew what they were doing.

photos.caption: Photo of Seafresh - London, United Kingdom

RZKvjRtN5IidGiXIAa2b-Q.text: Essentially a traditional fish and chips with take-out and restaurant...but also does 'proper' fish grilled at fancy plaice prices. My haddock managed to be both dry and watery at the same time - will stick with the battered stuff next time, if at all...

zbrzSK6i-bR2tuGq9hby8A.text: Excellent fish and chips. I got cod, and it was perfectly cooked. The fish was flaky, the batter was not too thick and cooked just right. Tartar sauce was good. For a starter, I got prawns in fillo dough, which wasn't quite what I expected: it was more of a Chinese food style batter than fillo dough. They were delicious as well. The staff was very polite and pleasant. The place has the ambience of an nice, but not upscale, chippy. I could peek into the kitchen and see a pretty chef, in chef clothing. That's a plus.

5bf-rd41bT3qgCLgmE3kGA.text: Wonderful fish and chips that are wayyyyyyyy over priced: a medium haddock with chips will run you 7.5 pds! Get the combo meal, it is plenty big for a meal and a solid value at 5 pds, with soft drink.Ketchup, tartar sauce etc will run you between 20 and 60 pence per pouch, which is insane. Also, be sure to check your order, because the counter woman has a tendency to "forget" to ad extras in. She will greet you with an Asian accented "You here for some fish, big boy?" that is worth a quid on its own.Ive only visited the a la carte side, the sit down looks to be a proper rip off.

t4IBhrVKwqqQ0WiZFoUFQw.text: The first thing I wanted to try when I got to the UK was fish and chips! I was so excited to see Yelp in London and even more so when I found this fish & chips place right around the corner of my hotel! The place looks very cute - there's a sit-down restaurant side and a fast-food counter where you can get some grub to go. We had to drag our luggage with us since our hotel was charging an arm and a leg to hold our bags for us and the hostess was nice enough to allow us to bring it to the restaurant. We had the lunch special - fish and chips (along with a side of green peas and white untoasted bread) with tea and dessert. It was . . . just okay. The fish was fried nicely and not too oily - I dunno what I was expecting out of it, but it tasted like something I could get in the States. Nothing out of this world. Blimey!

NS60JodTAu-sNbbeGg2ywA.text: We chose to sit in the dining room for dinner.  I don't know if the waitstaff plain forgot about us, or if we were just in a bad position, but it was tough to get someone's attention.But the food was delicious!  I have not had better fried fish in my life.  The batter was crisp, the fish (cod) was very soft and delicate, and the fries were excellent...even doused with malt vinegar.If I had to do it again, I would eat at Seafresh for sure, I would just plan on doing the takeout for half the price (10.95 for cod sitdown, 4.95 takeout!!!)

eLiY02NbEyyyAZ2cVR6Nrg.text: Maybe the best fish & chips in London.  A light tempura batter on fresh, flaky cod or haddock or salmon.  Takeout is great, but it's best when it comes right out of the fryer.

2cKToD9lVnv6doFZXiQeJA.text: I was really impressed with this place. The fish and chips were perfectly cooked and reasonably priced. I also liked the somewhat unusual lunch deal they had: fish and chips accompanied by a cup of tea and then followed by ice cream. The staff were friendly and quick to serve. I'd definitely go back.

PL4c084Ovglj4e5qisdiVQ.text: Good solid fish and chips here - but to be honest in my experience I think fish and chips are hard to get wrong or I've just been lucky and never been to a bad chippie.Wish it wasn't quite so pricey though - but I guess the location's partly to blame.

73-DwyLy2gEqpNh5_oW65A.text: Definitely not the cheapest fish and chips I've had, but certainly one of the most delicious I've tried, at least in Pimlico. I guess it makes sense when you see the place; it has a relatively nice decoration, trying to be minimalist, yet not quite, but hey who cares about decor when you are up for fish and chips. It's clean; it's fresh, and quite yummy.

photos.caption: Photo of Seafresh - London, United Kingdom

nKn7OsC1lcafQDsj_K7mdA.text: My first official fish and chips mission in London.  They have a takeout window on the left, and a restaurant on the right.  It was ok -- the fish was decent, the chips (fries where I'm from) were good.  Beer situation wasn't ideal (guinness in bottles, sigh), but would eat there again in a pinch.

VkU1Ogx7VWGF8rTzmHLtYA.text: I had their Fisherman's Pie. I thought it was pretty good. The very bottom is fish with some peas, carrot, and what seems like some crab meat as well topped off/crusted with what seems like some kind of mashed potatoes with cheese on top. It wasn't heavy and leaves a desire for more but it may be that it is the first time that I have had this. I saw some guy having some Fish and Chips and the size of the fish is actually very big so cost to value I think is quite good as well.

UV-OZC96gClG_cUawjnjgA.text: Seafresh was the first place my wife and ate on our trip to London since it was so close to our hotel. Everything was wonderful and it was exactly what we were expecting from a real British fish and chips restaurant. Friendly service, good fish, and a very fair price. Put those together and you have two very happy Americans.

A-jK0jAaEezf7-nuO_vIYg.text: Great food.  Small place. Friendly.   Try this place.  They are quick and the food taste good.  This is not a big expensive place.  This is family friendly neighborhood place.  Great fish and chips and other items were great.  I had the grilled calamari.

photos.caption: Photo of Seafresh - London, United Kingdom

ktRr6mQsu9MirICTS1bnNg.text: Found this fish & chips shop when looking for a nice bite near Victoria train station. Was excited by the yelp reviews, but upon sitting down in the restaurant realized that the dine-in prices were WAY higher than for take out. Was ready to spend 7 or 8 quid on fish & chips and when I sat down and read the menu, I realized it was going to set me back about £13! This is a huge difference and I would almost certainly order at the counter and take out next time. They even have a few stools and a narrow table along the front window where you can eat your take out.Happy to enjoy full table service, I decided on the Fish & Chips set menu: a medium cod or haddock, chips, peas, and bread and butter for £12.90. Not too bad. Plus it came with fruit or 2 scoops of ice cream and coffee or tea. Pretty good value and loads of food!I tried the haddock and a friend got the cod. We both got the same set menu, so it was strange when the plates came out and the haddock was almost twice the size as the cod. That being said, the cod definitely tasted better, with a nice flaky texture. The haddock was just bland and needed tons of salt to taste like anything at all. Even with the smaller piece of cod, it was enough food to fill your belly.Service was very good and friendly. 10% service change was automatically added to the bill.Next time, I'll order the cod and get it to go!

photos.caption: Photo of Seafresh - London, United Kingdom
Photo of Seafresh - London, United Kingdom. Set menu: best bargain in the place!
Photo of Seafresh - London, United Kingdom. Free olives for the table

JyhzjahTBJ6eLv9RYEKnIQ.text: Pricey for underwhelming food and not much atmosphere. I had haddock, which was in crisp batter and was nice and meaty. However, though the texture was great, it was very bland. Seriously. Always thought it was fairly easy to make fried fish delicious, and things like a good beer batter go far, but nothing about this has any taste. Chips were also disappointing and forgettable. The restaurant charges quite a lot for eating in, so it's definitely more than other similar places that are better quality. The woman serving us was friendly though.

VFJKAKQU_fWyOyMOes8kGg.text: Great fish and chips (got both the haddock and the cod) but even better staff. Very friendly and eager to share information on other places to go and see.

Ev26_dUIka7mSYB6jEsvsw.text: I know Seafresh specializes in Fish & Chips but we (my wife and I) had Catch of the Day (sea bass & tiger prawns).  It needed little more seasoning but was cook just right (tender and moist).  We plan to go back and try more of their dishes (perhaps their Fish & Chips).

photos.caption: Photo of Seafresh - London, United Kingdom. Sea bass and tiger prawns with spinach and new (baby) potatoes
Photo of Seafresh - London, United Kingdom. Specials for today and had the Catch of the day

3XVK8k6I4Pv2cOy6YEX3AA.text: We both had fried cod, small size. Staff were friendly and very helpful. Fish was delicious and was as much as we could eat. Highly recommended

zViaCGTV3qcyNO3vlTKWBg.text: Excellent fish and chips. Coworker was dead set on coming here as it has been highly recommended to him by a friend. I'm glad that we braved walk in the rain for this place - it was completely worth it (thank you, tube strike 2014).When the food came, it was a pleasant surprise. First of all - it smelled good. Radiant, really. Makes you want to eat it before eating it kind of maddening scent. Crunchy and flaky on the outside but moist on the inside when you bite into it. How is this possible? I don't know... magic, probably.

ARwYO4csiXJOLHytslNTyA.text: We got the cod fish and chips and the fish soup. The cod was extra fluffy and the batter was nice and crispy and light. I liked it... but the sauce it came with really didn't have much flavor. I think the chips could have been a bit more crispy, but I guess that's a bit hard when you have thick cut ones. The soup had a very interesting flavor. Not bad... just a flavor we've never had before. We were all able to drink it but were a bit confused on what we were drinking. My dad liked the fact that they had draft beer.

TbZ7uRJzDLBRbfQm_Iccyg.text: Thought the reviews oversold this place a little bit. We weren't that impressed. The restaurant prices were ridiculously higher than the take out prices. The fish and chips lunch price offer was good but...We ordered the haddock and our friends ordered the cod. The cod was absolutely tiny and the haddock was huge. For the same price. Not too impressed. The chips were really good and saved the day, proper fish and chip shop chips!Probably won't be coming here again.

uDNsMTs-Kmley41ys4InNg.text: A convenient walk from our Luna Simone hotel in Pimlico, this place was recommended in a Rick Steves guidebook. We ordered scallops and prawns with avocado for starters, then for the main meals seafood specials for two, fish and chips, and the lobster pasta. The food and service were great.

aDLADB_q6-ftN1DrOPRErA.text: I was staying right down the street from this restaurant. Figured if I'm in England I gotta try fish and chips. It was way more than I expected. Fresh fish and excellent service. What more can you ask for.

kwMM7Mzk62FPe9TvneBnpw.text: I found Seafresh through a top 10 fish & chips list for London. It was my first experience with fish & chips in London! And it was okay. When asked what we should order, the server said the cod is the most popular, and the haddock is also good if we want a "different taste." Well, I feel like the cod is popular because it's a standard... but it was a mistake to order it. Go for the haddock! It's a lot better.Got the fish and chips, dessert, and tea special, and that was it. My first fish & chips experience. It was everything I expected: fish fried just right, but average taste. Remember the haddoockkkkk.

DIbU_d-aLEugwc_GZQjE5Q.text: This review is for takeout. The fish was pretty good, light batter and fluffy, but for takeout I'm pretty sure they put it directly from the fryer into butcher paper - it was so oily and got a little soggy on the 10 minute walk home. Favorite was the cod, followed by the haddock. Wouldn't get skate again. Chips were just ok, would skip them next time (HUGE portions).

tNGfa7Gy4J-4NOEIitFsEg.text: Great fish and chips in the fish bar. The fish was moist in the middle and cooked to perfection with a werry crispy shell around. The chips was a bit soft en the shell but tastet great...

fyn1YVLGDeJz_dZ4Pt6PvQ.text: We arrived before 5PM on a Sunday evening. The greeter was very nice, and we were able to pick our table because other dinners hadn't arrived. It is an average sized restaurant with simple wooded table and chairs. It seemed very clean and you could see partially into the kitchen and that they were very good about washing their hands.  There is a "set menu" of 2 or 3 courses included that can save you a bit of money over ordering al'a carte. When we ordered there was considerable difficulty communicating with the waitress, there was a definite language issue, and I'm not sure what her first language was but she had difficulty understanding me and vice versa.       I wasn't sure what would arrive at the table but it was close to what I tried to ask for, not sure why it was complicated, it just seemed like neither of us was sure that the other meant.  One item that was ordered was a prawn salad, which arrived as mostly lettuce with tiny prawns to give it a sense of being legitimate, but far too much Thousand Island dressing, it should have been on the side, but I think it was an effort to hide the parsimonious amount of shrimp.  The main dish was generous on the other items however and the fish (Halibut and Cod) were perfect.       However my husband did not order the batter covered style but we both got that in the end.  Who knows where communications broke down.  The peas seemed fresh and the chips were maybe a tad undercooked, but nothing terrible.  The staff is extremely friendly and check on you, but you are reluctant to say much because who knows what they will assume.  My husband asked for a glass of water and I swear I thought the waiter repeated "Hot Water?" but he did actually get a glass of water.  We asked for tea and got a ready made cup of milky tea.  It was fine but I thought it unusual to not be asked if we wanted milk (I didn't, but I drank it because it wasn't worth trying to explain).      Another couple came in and seemed very familiar with the staff and was treated with great attention and consideration, their extended family arrived shortly, their daughter and two grandsons, about 4 and 3.  They knew the staff and were happy to see them.  It was impressive how kind the staff were.  However the kids were raucous to the point of being a disruption and I realized that they cater to families, so I wouldn't take a new date there, generally speaking.  I think it was a reasonable meal, but for me, without children of a certain age, I wouldn't go there except for take away.

ftentH18f11pHp3ow_3V9w.text: Exceptional food and service. A must visit in London. Lucky for us it was just around the corner from our hotel

photos.caption: Photo of Seafresh - London, United Kingdom
Photo of Seafresh - London, United Kingdom. Haddock & chips

B2PqwgGTKf4NXhnKR1aqeg.text: Walked by this place on a misty London night( what misty in London ??) order the Scottish salmon, grilled 1 £ surcharge and fried prawns. Chips came with meal.  The seating is basic , bright and clean. Fresh fish offerings as well the fish and chips. Service friendly and wee bit hectic. My salmon was over cooked. But there was plenty of it. The prawns were huge with a tasty batter.

ouZuBhYH6dbIsQRDtgZGNA.text: Fish and chips -- 4.5 stars.  Very tasty.  Perfectly done.  I devoured everything.  The teens had roasted chicken.  Really tasty, perfectly done.   Four stars.Beer was good. Only two on tap.  The bitter was nice with the fish and chips.  Three stars.  This is not a fish and chips and beer pub.Atmosphere -- three stars.  Friendly, nice, open, lots of space.  Nothing spectacular...didn't feel really British, which as US visitors, we were looking for, but not a negative.  Good place.Price -- high!  We dropped 85 pounds for two roasted chickens, two F&C and two beers!    I like the place a lot, but that price tag really hurt!

tzJVz1StQuviRlY-MSAfgw.text: Pimlico chippy, Seafresh Seafresh?!After reading the reviews, I was expecting better, yes. You can get the nitty gritty deets from the other Yelp crew. But let me just tell you what I thought of the service and food. THE GOOD: Very pleasant staff, cordial and niceI was greeted straight away, no 'tude no krazee eyes Had so much hope for the place, thought it would be fly But I felt like my trip was a waste of time. THE BAD: Looked at the menu and ordered the number one Cod and chips with bread and a drink of choice, done and done. Looked at the eat in prices and nearly tripped my wallet imploded, bank account exploded and I did a backflip THE UGLY: I was starving, but took it to goBegan dining immediately when I reached homeBut sadly nothing could save this grand fish dishIt could not be resuscitated, limp, lifeless, tastelessand boy, oh boy i hate to say it, but felt like I was chewing on a rubber toy.and in it, I found three bones!Terrified, I screamed like that kid in the scene of Home AloneMy bread was okay, it was pre-butteredFor which I am grateful, I'm no diet nutter The fries tasted processed instead of fresh cutTo save them, a hearty dumping of ketchup. I know I'm outta line. But the best part of my meal was the Heinz.

rTKafItoL6YbH3BhW1HAAw.text: Tempura style fish and chips. Hot hot hot. Flaky and delicious. Best to eat in the restaurant. Absolutely the best fish and chips in London.

cM5UBGUzi7NKDWNNxnU3ig.text: One of my go to places for fish & chips when I stay near Victoria for work.  Never too greasy, relatively cheap and so far always good.  It's fried fish, so if that's what you're expecting you won't be disappointed.  I never specify which fish and I have no idea which one I'm getting, but if it ain't broke don't fix it.  Give it a try.

NyoRcKv4_CxbFrsXfWbhpA.text: Amazing fresh seafood, we tried the prawn with avocado, the oak smoked salmon salad, and the cod fish and chips. All were delicious and we ate every bit of it. Their ice cream was refreshing for dessert, especially the strawberry. Their service was very friendly and attentive, would recommend 100% to anyone looking for seafood.

photos.caption: Photo of Seafresh - London, United Kingdom
Photo of Seafresh - London, United Kingdom
Photo of Seafresh - London, United Kingdom

pdPkpWuuqt6BrfPv2lmxdw.text: I eat here from time to time and it's pretty good as more up-market fish & chip establishments go, but I've never quite understood why the place gets so many rave reviews here and elsewhere. The standard cod or whatever and chips is decent enough, but a bit pricy compared to a more basic chippie where the quality may be as good or better. The upside is you can get a decent glass of wine with your meal, and the value seems to improve as you progress up the menu. Best choice in my view is the skate, either grilled or fried it's a good value option.Generally this place is good but it's not one of the best in town.

mfDH3_oJggqVqntHjw3WCQ.text: Excellent Fish & Chips. Huge piece of fish, chips are great too. Wife had the Catch of the Day; grilled fillet of seabass & prawns, potatoes and spinach. Friendly service, especially from our waiter Ruben! Very welcoming and humorous. Provided tips for our next vacation!  Thank you!

photos.caption: Photo of Seafresh - London, United Kingdom. Front counter

YRayMKIxE6jM0YJEFZEPRw.text: The menu was wide ranging and I love me some seafood, but this place was good but not great. The service was great and I felt well cared for which isn't always the case when you're dining alone.  I started with the prawn avocado appetizer which was very bland (with rose marie sauce which as I suspected is a mix of mayo and ketchup) but the shrimp were good. Then I had the crab linguine special and mushy peas (since those seem to be a thing). The linguine was OK and crab wasn't that flavorful. As for mushy peas, they tasted OK, but I think you must have to be raised with those to really crave them plus the side portion was HUGE, especially for £2.80. I did have a lovely cup of tea so that was good. Maybe I would have been better off going with fried dishes.

photos.caption: Photo of Seafresh - London, United Kingdom. Prawn and avocado app

i8Yuq0uLQvPV9NciVIphiQ.text: This is apparently THE place for Fish and Chips in London (#1 in London and in the top 5 in the UK).  We went early (between 1700 and 1800) and it was easy to get a table.  The calamari was awesome, as was the fish and chips.  You can choose (cod and hake the night we were there).  The hake had a lighter taste but more compact texture.  The cod had the flakier fish texture.  The waitress described the hake as more "fishy" but I associate that description with a heavy fish taste, not texture...so I thought I'd explicate here.  Bottom line, both were good.  The serving sizes were HUGE.  We ended up eating only half.

photos.caption: Photo of Seafresh - London, United Kingdom

2rui87A7470m5apUyir35A.text: When I visited London, I heard I had to get some fish and chips.  Seafresh was the spot to grab fish and chips.  The customer service was phenomenal.  When I visit again, I will definitely be back!

photos.caption: Photo of Seafresh - London, United Kingdom. I simply enjoyed the excellent customer service as well as the delicious meal!
Photo of Seafresh - London, United Kingdom

E5Ci8dnK8E43aAognIGbHg.text: This establishment came highly recommended for tasting fish and chips in London!  It is tucked away in the Victoria area, not hard to find at all!  The portions were huge,  and my fish was outstanding!  I would dedinitely recommend this place to others.  The customer service was awesome, and our waitress was very helpful and well informed.  Several employees checked on the table and made our dining experience truly special.

photos.caption: Photo of Seafresh - London, United Kingdom

BktllT3_uV3Za_5K71Xhxg.text: Fish and chips was one of the best I have ever eaten.  The haddock was fresh and tasty.  My wife had the cod, which was also excellent.  The haddock had a slight fishy taste, but in a good way. The service was friendly and helpful.

photos.caption: Photo of Seafresh - London, United Kingdom. Great fish and chips

N2OFdCwHAr4u_ydZ2hVZ3g.text: Very good seafood! I had a taste of my mom's fish soup that she ordered, and it was very delicious and flavorful. I got the medium Cod Fish & Chips, and the fish was nice and soft, tasty too. Our waiter (Ruben) was very friendly, he chatted with us about seafood and gave us travel tips.

XUhhCQuAov144d-O7lFXRQ.text: Had lunch - Grilled SeaBass with shrimp nicely prepared! Sautéed spinach and new potatoes.... I would recommend and will visit again!

gubElUf3j6T53w3jvI8Rsg.text: Amazing fish and chips and deep fried whitebait. Our waiter was so friendly too.  The service was a little slow, but that is to be expected in London.  The food was very fresh like it was just caught. Definitely recommend! Will come back again!

photos.caption: Photo of Seafresh - London, United Kingdom. Deep-fried Whitebait
Photo of Seafresh - London, United Kingdom. Haddock Fish and Chips
Photo of Seafresh - London, United Kingdom

xk_rC_hZvxjlgj0bmptgQg.text: My local fish and chips shop.Never disappoints. Consistent quality , great portions and not so bad prices.Staff is friendly as well.

yJIaay8uVwGOExtJlsyAzg.text: I was near the Victoria Station and looked online for the best restaurant in the area. Seafresh popped up and I went. Martha sat us down and I must say, she surprised us with a smile and friendly service. We had been in london for 4 days by this point and each restaurant we went to received us with scowls and unfriendliness. Martha was very nice. Throughout our meal, she checked in to make sure we were enjoying our food without being too overbearing. I don't don't what to say but that Martha redeemed all of London for us! Now, let's talk about the food. I had salmon with a side of salad. Very good. My dining partner had tried the fish and chips at a different restaurants the other day but was quite disappointed. This time, he decided to try a different kind of fish--kind of an alternative to fish and chips. He ordered the deep fried scampi. It was delicious! We also ordered the Mediterranean Serving Platter for our appetizer (they call it a starter in England). That was delicious, too!All in all, I had a pleasurable experience. Well, to say that it was just "pleasurable" doesn't do it justice. The food was excellent and Martha's service was exquisite. If you go and Martha is working, you will receive the best night of your life! It's the professionalism and care that she puts into her job that truly made the night for us.

photos.caption: Photo of Seafresh - London, United Kingdom. Deep-fried scampi was to die for!
Photo of Seafresh - London, United Kingdom. Salmon with salad

AnH-WxppeE-oXyxSbYVQyw.text: First time this American enjoyed a proper fish and chips while visiting London and we really enjoyed. The batter was so light and crispy; the cod was fluffy and dense as it should be. Nice flavor overall. Great portion. My husband had the ginormous order of plaice (flounder) and loved every bite he could handle. I forgot to mention our starter - calamari. Really fresh serving of calamari with the same crispy batter and amazing tartar sauce. We loved it all!! The best part of our visit? The service. Loved chatting it up with the guys there asking about the area, London food, etc. So glad our Air BNB host suggested this spot!

photos.caption: Photo of Seafresh - London, United Kingdom. Plaice (flounder)
Photo of Seafresh - London, United Kingdom. Calamari

HG-5pQFjIt877BgcFsPBfA.text: Everything was really good!! Definitely a comfortable spot for someone traveling alone to feel comfortable!! :)

VU0n7uX81MPosjnkCXaBYA.text: Mediocre service and food.  We ate here our last night in the UK expecting to get a really good meal and finish our trip with great British service.  It never happened.  The server barely understood English, which seems to be a reoccurring theme in England (this is not good irony when trying to get proper answers before ordering).  She couldn't understand nor answer our questions about the specials, and which wines paired well with them.  The manager or owner (he never identified himself) came out and then somewhat curtly responded to our questions.  After that, we waited and waited for service (I think the [only] wait staff there was afraid to approach us again).  Finally, the owner/manager noticed us staring at them for service, and (they) took our order. When the food arrived, it was mediocre- the fish and chips were somewhat chewy (too battered).  My salad wasn't very good (brown lettuce) and over-priced scallops weren't the freshest- geeze, this is England, where the most furthest point inland is 70 miles- why is it so hard to find fresh seafood??  The asparagus side was properly done, but that and the wine recommendation were the only good things I can remember from this eatery, as we left after paying a hefty bill and feeling a bit let-down about our experience.

pvgcCayN6pX28NA7AyxcHA.text: This sounds silly but the reason why it's a no-brainer for me to go back to London later this year for another NFL game when I'm not even a fan is because of Seafresh!A local recommended this place who told us that the best fish and chips can be found at a "chippy" - such as Seafresh ("If you find yourself at a nice, restaurant...you're in the WRONG place!").  Seafresh serves huge portions of perfectly fried, thick and juicy fish coated in a thin crispy batter...you can actually taste the fish!  Not only was the food superb, the people behind the counter were so friendly.  Visited: October 2014 and October 2015 (had to!)

photos.caption: Photo of Seafresh - London, United Kingdom. Friendly service
Photo of Seafresh - London, United Kingdom. Perfection!

5zQJ0sxNwtNlVNbPzeAV4A.text: "London's best fish and chips" NotCod was very dense and stiff. Skate is not great deep fried, very mushy and soft.  was my mistake to be too adventurous. Just not the quality for what they charge. But the waiter was nice. Londoner avoid

photos.caption: Photo of Seafresh - London, United Kingdom. Deep fried skate. Mushy and soft....

NSzE5UTFpJqo_U4rcBsRCQ.text: I ate at the counter next store, not at the sit down part of the restaurant. I ordered fish and chips. It was delicious! Fish was hot, flaky and moist. Chips were steaming hot. All around a good meal.

photos.caption: Photo of Seafresh - London, United Kingdom. Fish and chips
